This paper focuses on the analysis of malware samples in enterprise networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses social engineering tactics used by attackers, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of time-series data and vulnerability analysis could also fall under the categories of social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
